net.sf.jclec.mo.algorithm

Class MOPSOAlgorithm

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.jclec.algorithm.AbstractAlgorithm
      • net.sf.jclec.algorithm.PSOAlgorithm
        • net.sf.jclec.mo.algorithm.MOPSOAlgorithm
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, net.sf.jclec.IAlgorithm, net.sf.jclec.IConfigure, net.sf.jclec.JCLEC, IMOAlgorithm

    public class MOPSOAlgorithm
extends PSOAlgorithm
implements IMOAlgorithm
    A generic PSO algorithm to solve multi-objective problems. It implements the general optimization process, where the selection of leaders, the management of the archive, the update of the velocities and positions and the execution of the optional turbulence mechanism are delegated to the multi-objective strategy.

    HISTORY:

    • (AR|JRR|SV, 1.0, March 2018) First release.

    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Aurora Ramirez (AR), Jose Raul Romero (JRR), Sebastian Ventura (SV)

    Knowledge Discovery and Intelligent Systems (KDIS) Research Group: http://www.uco.es/grupos/kdis

    See Also:
    IMOAlgorithm, PSOAlgorithm, MOPSOStrategy, Serialized Form
